cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a fully convolutional neural network approach for automatic segmentation and identification of vertebrae in medical images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a memory component and iterative instance segmentation approach also suggests relevance to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves regression tasks, which could be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
